//walk test page parameters Step %1$s of %2$s Walk Test This function allows you to measure your walking ability. This is important because PAD affects your ability to walk. Walk Test Location The test is best performed in an outside area that is flat and where you will not be slowed down or obstructed by the environment or other people. Walk Test Instructions The object of this test is to walk as far as possible for 6 minutes. You should not run or jog. Six minutes is a long time to walk, so you will be exerting yourself. You may get out of breath or develop leg pain. You can slow down, stop, and rest if needed, but you should resume walking as soon as you are able. Walk Test Pain Button During the 6-minute walk test, you will have an option to indicate when you have first experienced leg pain. If you want to use this option, please press the pain button, which is shown below, when you first notice leg pain. Walk Test â€“ Ready? When you are ready to go, press the START button below and wait for a count down to 3. Your phone will beep and vibrate signaling u to start walking. when the 6 minutes is over, at which time the test is complete and you will be able to check your results.
